content:
Route cases from your customer support emails to qualified agents with an Omni-Channel flow.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
Customize Application
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud

Use an Omni-Channel flow rather than a record-triggered flow to direct cases to the right queue or agent. Avoid using other case assignment rules so that Email-to-Case routes cases using the logic in your Omni-Channel flow.

Inside the Omni-Channel flow you can build logic to route, or you can choose to not route the case. If an exception occurs while the flow executes, then the case is routed to the fallback queue.

Assign the Run Flows or Manage Flows permission to the automated case user.

From Setup, create or edit the routing address that your customers use to submit inquiries to your support team.
Specify the flow created to route cases in the Flow Settings section and a fallback queue with an Omni-Channel routing configuration.
Click Save.

When a customer sends an email, Email-to-Case creates a case if one doesn't exist. The flow then executes and directs the case to the appropriate Omni-Channel queue or agent.
title: Assigning Omni-Channel Flows for Case Routing
